Swift Swim

Passive Ability

When damaged by a Pokémon from the opposing team; increases movement speed by 40% for 2s, decaying by 10% every 0.5s (minimum 25% increased movement speed) (10s CD).

This Pokémon's headache gauge increases by 1% for every 0.5% max HP damage received by Psyduck or nearby ally Pokémon from Pokémon on the opposing team. This gauge fills at a rate of 30% per 1s (requiring a total of 3.33s to fully charge). When the headache gauge is full, a mysterious power is triggered, interrupting Psyduck from casting moves, cleansing status conditions on themself, becoming unstoppable and decreasing their movement speed by 30% for 1s; then shoving nearby opposing Pokémon away for 0.8s, and resetting this Pokémon's move cooldowns. The mysterious power stays active for 10s, boosting moves and giving them 20% cooldown reduction. When the mysterious power ends, Psyduck cannot use moves or attacks, or charge their headache gauge for 2.5s.

Attack

Auto Attack

Attacks with a shot of water.

Psyduck has no boosted attack.

Confusion

Move 1

6.00s Ranged

Releases a weak telekinetic force in the designated direction, damaging opposing Pokémon and stunning them for 1s when it hits.

While the mysterious power is active, deals increased damage.

70% SpA + 3 x (Level - 1) + 380

84% SpA + 3 x (Level - 1) + 456

Confusion Upgrade Choices

Surf

7.00s Hindrance

Creates a wave in the designated direction, damaging opposing Pokémon and decreasing their movement speed by 30% for 2.5s when it hits; if opposing Pokémon already have their movement speed decreased when this move hits, they are also shoved for 0.5s. Rides the wave for at least 0.4s and until this move is used again or for up to 5s, moving forward and increasing movement speed by 30%; the user can use basic attacks and moves while riding the wave. Ally Pokémon who touch the wave while Psyduck is riding it have their movement speed increased by 70% for 3s (decaying by 10% every 0.5s over 2s; minimum 30%). When this move is used again, stops in place and creates another wave in the designated direction.

While the mysterious power is active, creates two waves in the designated direction each time this move is used.

65% SpA + 4 x (Level - 1) + 304

45% SpA + 3 x (Level - 1) + 212

Decreases the damage dealt by opposing Pokémon hit by this move by 25% for 2.5s.

Bubble Beam

6.50s Ranged

Forcefully ejects a spray of bubbles in the designated direction, damaging opposing Pokémon in the area of effect and attaching a mark with 3 bubbles to those hit for 5s. When a teammate damages opposing Pokémon with bubbles attached to them with auto attacks, a bubble bursts, damaging the target. When all bubbles on a target burst from auto attack damage, they are stunned for 0.5s and their movement speed is decreased by 30% for 2s.

While the mysterious power is active, strengthens the damage dealt when bubbles burst.

80% SpA + 4 x (Level - 1) + 360

40% SpA + 2 x (Level - 1) + 180

96% SpA + 5 x (Level - 1) + 432

48% SpA + 2 x (Level - 1) + 216

Decreases the movement speed of opposing Pokémon hit by the beam by 30% for 2s.

Tail Whip

Move 2

6.00s Sure Hit

Wags their tail at the designated opposing Pokémon, damaging them and decreasing their movement speed by 30% and their Sp. Def by 20% for 2s.

While the mysterious power is active, strengthens the Sp. Def decrease to 30%.

60% SpA + 2 x (Level - 1) + 320

Tail Whip Upgrade Choices

Disable

8.00s Hindrance

Releases electricity at the designated opposing Pokémon, damaging the target and stunning them for 0.2s. Opposing Pokémon hit by the electricity from this use of the move have a mark applied to them for 5s which has a disabling effect tied to it; the disabling effect increases the cooldown of the last move used by a marked target by 2s, or the next move used if no move is on cooldown (once only). When the disabling effect occurs, the target's movement speed is also decreased by 30% for 2s. The electricity spreads to a nearby opposing Pokémon up to 4 times; the electricity can only spread to the same target once.

While the mysterious power is active, the electricity can spread up to 6 times; the electricity can spread to the same target up to 2 times.

54.4% SpA + 3 x (Level - 1) + 260

Strengthens the stun duration to 0.5s.

Psychic

7.50s Hindrance

Decreases movement speed by 10% and releases a strong telekinetic force in the designated area, damaging opposing Pokémon in the area of effect and stunning them for 1s when it hits. Continues to release a telekinetic force at the Pokémon from the opposing team closest to the center of the area of effect when this move hits, marking them for 2s. If this move is used again or after 2s and the user is in range of the marked target, pulls the target a set distance in the designated direction (pulling them toward the user's location if no direction is designated), stunning them for 0.85s during the pull.

While the mysterious power is active, stuns the target marked by this move for 0.2s after being pulled.

103.5% SpA + 9 x (Level - 1) + 495

Decreases the Sp. Def of opposing Pokémon hit by the area of effect by 25% for 2s.

Full-Power Psy-ay-ay!

Unite Move

112s 100000 Hindrance

Unlocks at level 8

Releases three mysterious psychic waves around themself, damaging opposing Pokémon in the area of effect and decreasing the damage dealt by them by 25% for 3s when hit.

After using this Unite Move, increases the headache gauge by 50% as a consequence of Psyduck unleashing their full power.

60% SpA + 6 x (Level - 1) + 300

Unite Buffs (6s duration):

30% Movement Speed, 30% CDR, 20% Max HP Shield
